The paper deals with the problem of semantic labeling of 3D point clouds using a novel 1D-fully convolutional network. This involves processing unordered point sets with varying densities, without relying on expensive hand-crafted features. The paper also discusses the use of spectral data for feature extraction. Given these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with geometric reasoning (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) to some extent, which are also possible sub-categories.
